# ============================================================================
# PRIVATE DIRECTORY - SENSITIVE CONTENT PROTECTION
# ============================================================================
# This .gitignore ensures that sensitive files placed in this directory
# are NEVER committed to Git or pushed to GitHub.
#
# WHAT THIS PROTECTS:
# - Proprietary technical designs
# - Sensitive data models and architectures
# - API keys, credentials, and secrets
# - Private business information
# - Personal or confidential documents
#
# ============================================================================

# Ignore ALL files and directories by default
*

# EXCEPTIONS: Allow these specific files to be tracked
!.gitignore
!README.md

# Allow subdirectories themselves to be tracked (but not their contents)
# Each subdirectory should have its own .gitignore
!*/

# ============================================================================
# VERIFICATION: To verify this is working, run:
#   git status
# 
# You should ONLY see .gitignore and README.md as trackable files.
# All other content should be ignored.
# ============================================================================

